metadata.ames: true == ames running, false == pypower running opf
metadata.solver: The name for the solver for ames
metadata.priceSensLoad: true == Substation load is flexible, false == only inflexible load
metadata.windPower: true == wind power, false == no wind power
metadata.noScale: FNCS gld_scale set to 1 if false
metadata.curve: FNCS no curve if set to false
metadata.zonalReserves: true = has zonal reserves, false == does not have zonal reserves
metadata.StartTime: Start time for the simulation run in the form of YYYY-MM-DD HH:MM:SS
metadata.EndTime: End time for the simulation run in the form of YYYY-MM-DD HH:MM:SS
metadata.Tmax: The duration for the simulation in seconds
metadata.Period: Time interval for the simulation in seconds for opf/ames
metadata.dt: The delta time for the simulation in seconds for pf
metadata.zones: An array for each zone [zone id, name, ReserveDownZonalPercent, ReserveUpZonalPercent]
bus: Gs -shunt conductance (MW demanded at V = 1.0 p.u.)
Bs -shunt susceptance (MVAr injected at V = 1.0 p.u.)
LAM P -Lagrange multiplier on real power mismatch (u/MW)
LAM Q -Lagrange multiplier on reactive power mismatch (u/MVAr)
gen: mBase -total MVA base of machine, defaults to baseMVA
status -machine status > 0 = machine in-service, machine status, 0 = machine out-of-service
PC1* -lower real power output of PQ capability curve (MW)
PC2* -upper real power output of PQ capability curve (MW)
QC1MIN* -minimum reactive power output at PC1 (MVAr)
QC1MAX* -maximum reactive power output at PC1 (MVAr)
QC2MIN* -minimum reactive power output at PC2 (MVAr)
QC2MAX* -maximum reactive power output at PC2 (MVAr)
RAMP AGC* -ramp rate for load following/AGC (MW/min)
RAMP Q* -ramp rate for reactive power (2 sec timescale) (MVAr/min)
metadata.gencost: An array for each generator cost [2, startup, shutdown, 3, c2, c1, c0]
metadata.branch: An array for each branch [from bus id, to bus id, r, x, b, rateA, rateB, rateC, ratio, angle, status, angmin, angmax]
metadata.DSO: An array for each substation instance [bus id, name, gld_scale, Pnom, Qnom, curve_scale, curve_skew, Pinit, Qinit]
metadata.UnitsOut: An array for each units out[idx, time out[s], time back in[s]]
metadata.BranchesOut: An array for each branches out [idx, time out[s], time back in[s]]
